Vodacom announced that it will implement a below-inflation average price increase on selected packages on 1 April 2019. No specific details on the price increases were provided at the time, and the announcement was made as part of a statement on new out-of-bundle (OOB) data rates. The network has now informed customers about which packages will be affected, and created a webpage that details the new pricing. “With effect from the 1st April 2019, your monthly subscription and certain value added services will be increasing,” said Vodacom. “We have ensured that the price increase is below inflation in order to ensure our customers stay connected at the best value.” New prices The tables below detail Vodacom’s new pricing. Top Up/uChoose Pricing 12-month data contracts <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-302284" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-Month-Data-Contracts-Incl-Top-Up.png" alt="" width="840" height="830" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-Month-Data-Contracts-Incl-Top-Up.png 840w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-Month-Data-Contracts-Incl-Top-Up-300x296.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-Month-Data-Contracts-Incl-Top-Up-768x759.png 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/12-Month-Data-Contracts-Incl-Top-Up-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> 24-month data contracts <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-302282" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/24-Month-Data-Contracts-Incl-Top-Up.png" alt="" width="842" height="828" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/24-Month-Data-Contracts-Incl-Top-Up.png 842w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/24-Month-Data-Contracts-Incl-Top-Up-300x295.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019